# Verification Model

Verification reconstructs the canonical signed payload directly from exported receipt data.

Verification performs independent evaluation of:

• Canonical payload reconstruction

• SHA-256 digest recomputation

• Digital signature validation

• Issuer trust evaluation

• Evidence manifest validation

• Receipt integrity

Results intentionally distinguish:

• Content integrity

• Signer recognition

• Device authorization claims

• Authorization acceptance

rather than collapsing multiple guarantees into one verification result.

---

# Local-First Security Model

SYNC minimizes trust assumptions.

Receipt creation requires no backend.

Receipt storage defaults to the user's device.

Evidence remains under user control.

Verification occurs independently of the originating application.

The project avoids cloud custody wherever possible.

---

# Interoperability

SYNC is intentionally designed as a composable authorization evidence system.

The repository separates:

• human review evidence

• presentation evidence

• device authorization

from organizational policy, execution, and enforcement systems.

Independent receipt systems may bind to the same underlying action through cryptographic digest relationships while remaining independently verifiable under separate trust roots.

The repository therefore supports interoperability without requiring participating systems to merge trust models or surrender independent verification.

---

